aa(lp48
VNow, the reason for this, the reason that the fashion industry
p49
aVdoesn't have any copyright protection
p50
aVis because the courts decided long ago
p51
aVthat apparel is too utilitarian
p52
aVto qualify for copyright protection.
p53
aVThey didn't want a handful of designers
p54
aVowning the seminal building blocks of our clothing.
p55
aVAnd then everybody else would have to license this cuff or this sleeve
p56
aVbecause Joe Blow owns it.
p57
aVBut too utilitarian? I mean is that the way you think of fashion?
p58
aVThis is Vivienne Westwood. No!
p59
aVWe think of it as maybe too silly,
p60
aVtoo unnecessary.
