aa(lp62
VNow, those of you who are familiar with the logic
p63
aVbehind copyright protection \u2014
p64
aVwhich is that without ownership, there is no incentive to innovate \u2014
p65
aVmight be really surprised
p66
aVby both the critical success of the fashion industry
p67
aVand the economic success of this industry.
p68
aVWhat I'm going to argue today is that
p69
aVbecause there's no copyright protection
p70
aVin the fashion industry,
p71
aVfashion designers have actually been able to elevate
p72
aVutilitarian design,
p73
aVthings to cover our naked bodies,
p74
aVinto something that we consider art.
p75
aVBecause there's no copyright protection
p76
aVin this industry,
p77
aVthere's a very open and creative
p78
aVecology of creativity.
